<para><anchor id="index_1md__2home_2loic_2EPITECH_2rtype_2Mystic-Type_2README"/> Multiplayer R-Type-like with an authoritative TCP/UDP server and a raylib graphical client.</para>
<sect1 id="index_1autotoc_md1">
<title>Prerequisites</title>
<sect2 id="index_1autotoc_md2">
<title>All Platforms</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>CMake ≥ 3.14</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>C++17 compiler</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>raylib (fetched automatically via FetchContent)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect2>
<sect2 id="index_1autotoc_md3">
<title>Windows-Specific Prerequisites</title>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><bold>CMake</bold> ≥ 3.14<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Download: <ulink url="https://cmake.org/download/">https://cmake.org/download/</ulink></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Add CMake to PATH during installation</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Visual Studio 2022</bold> (recommended) or <bold>MinGW</bold><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Visual Studio 2022 Community (free): <ulink url="https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/">https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/</ulink></para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Required workload: &quot;Desktop development with C++&quot;</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>Alternative: MinGW-w64 (<ulink url="https://www.mingw-w64.org/">https://www.mingw-w64.org/</ulink>)</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><bold>Git for Windows</bold> (optional, for cloning)<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>Download: <ulink url="https://git-scm.com/download/win">https://git-scm.com/download/win</ulink></para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para><bold>Note:</bold> The build script will attempt Visual Studio 17 2022 or Visual Studio 16 2019 generators first, then fall back to MinGW Makefiles if Visual Studio is not installed.</para>
</sect2>
</sect1>
